article.headline: Drake 79, Evansville 68
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- Chris Bryant scored 15 points, including six during a decisive 12-0 run, to lead Drake to a 79-68 victory over Evansville Wednesday night in the Missouri Valley Conference opener for both teams. Ajay Calvin scored 14 for the Bulldogs (8-4, 1-0 MVC). Al Stewart had 13 and Chaun Brooks 11 for Drake, which led 33-31 at halftime. The teams exchanged the lead twice and were tied six times during the first half. The Bulldogs regained the lead with 3:45 left in the half when a 3-pointer by Brooks made it 27-24. The Purple Aces (4-5, 0-1) took a 34-33 lead after the break when Bradley Strickland sank a free throw and then hit a jumper. But Bryant hit a 3-pointer seconds later that began 12 unanswered points and gave the Bulldogs a 45-34 lead with 13:33 left. Evansville never drew closer than six points for rest of the game. Jason Holsinger led the Purple Aces with 18, including 3-of-8 3-pointers. Strickland scored 15, Ely Shy 14 and Matt Webster 11.
